pageContext.claim: “We're straightening it out, and it's getting done and you see what's going with China we're taking in, we will soon be taken in over $100 billion in tariffs.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump's claim that his tariffs on China will raise $100 billion is not credible. That would more than double the current annual level of customs duties. According to Treasury Department data, overall tariff revenue collected in the latest fiscal year — on imports from China and the rest of the world — is just a drop in the fiscal bucket.
